Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Tenecin 1 (3S=S, natural AMPs; defensin, UCSS1a;  insects, arthropods, invertebrates, animals)
Sequence Information.Crucial residues: S-S bonds are critical since reduced tenecin is not antimicrobial.

Literature Information.Literature: Chemical modification:  It contains three disulfide bonds.Activity: active against S. aureus ATCC 6538 (MIC 6.25 ug/ml), MRSA (MMIC 25 ug/ml), M. luteus ATCC 9341 (MIC 3.12 ug/ml), E.coli ATCC 2592 (MIC>100 ug/ml), P.aeruginosa ATCC 9027 (MIC > 100 ug/ml), and C.albicans ATCC 36232 (MIC > 100 ug/ml).Updated 11/2024
Literature Information.Author: Moon HJ., Lee SY., Kurata S., Natori S., Lee BL1994
Literature Information.Title: Purification and molecular cloning of cDNA for an inducible antibacterial protein from larvae of the coleopteran, Tenebrio molitor.
